      <div class="em-body">
        <p class="em-lead">We welcome the whole school to the church on a weekly basis, where the Eucharist is celebrated on the first Monday of the month.</p>
        <p>At weekly Collective Worship we make a point of introducing the pupils to the liturgy and doctrines that shape our faith, so that church will be a place that feels familiar to them for the rest of their lives. Our services include lively music, readings and prayers led by the pupils, and a strong emphasis on fostering curiosity and wonder.</p>

        <h3>Applying through the church route</h3>
        <p>If you are considering applying for a place at Emmanuel School for your child, please make very sure that you familiarise yourself with the admissions criteria.</p>
        <p>To apply via the church route, you and your child will need to attend a Eucharistic service six times a quarter for the eight successive quarters prior to the date of application. In other words: if you want a place for September 2028, you will apply in January 2028 and will need to have been attending twice a month since January 2026.</p>
        <p>If you have any questions regarding the church side of the admissions process, or about registering your child's attendance at church, please speak to the vicar.</p>

        <div class="em-placeholder" style="margin-top:14px"><p>Link to the school website and to Emmanuel School's admissions policy to follow.</p></div>
